TABLE OF CONTENTS

CARD MEMBER AND OTHER LOANS

CARD MEMBER LOANS, REPRESENTING REVOLVING AMOUNTS DUE ON LENDING CARD PRODUCTS, ARE RECORDED AT THE TIME A CARD MEMBER ENTERS INTO A

POINT-OF-SALE TRANSACTION WITH A MERCHANT, AS WELL AS AMOUNTS DUE FROM CHARGE CARD MEMBERS WHO UTILIZE THE LENDING-ON-CHARGE FEATURE ON THEIR ACCOUNT AND ELECT TO REVOLVE A PORTION OF THE OUTSTANDING BALANCE BY ENTERING INTO A REVOLVING PAYMENT

ARRANGEMENT WITH THE COMPANY. THESE LOANS HAVE A RANGE OF TERMS SUCH AS CREDIT LIMITS, INTEREST RATES, FEES AND PAYMENT STRUCTURES, WHICH CAN BE REVISED OVER TIME BASED ON NEW INFORMATION ABOUT CARD MEMBERS AND IN ACCORDANCE WITH APPLICABLE

REGULATIONS AND THE RESPECTIVE PRODUCTS TERMS AND CONDITIONS. CARD MEMBERS HOLDING REVOLVING LOANS ARE TYPICALLY REQUIRED TO MAKE MONTHLY PAYMENTS BASED ON PRE-ESTABLISHED AMOUNTS. THE AMOUNTS THAT CARD MEMBERS CHOOSE TO REVOLVE ARE SUBJECT TO

FINANCE CHARGES.

CARD MEMBER LOANS ARE PRESENTED ON THE CONSOLIDATED BALANCE SHEETS NET OF RESERVES FOR LOSSES (REFER TO

NOTE 4), AND INCLUDE PRINCIPAL, ACCRUED INTEREST AND FEES RECEIVABLE. THE COMPANYS POLICY GENERALLY IS TO CEASE ACCRUING INTEREST ON A CARD MEMBER LOAN AT THE TIME THE ACCOUNT IS WRITTEN OFF, AND ESTABLISH RESERVES FOR INTEREST THAT THE

COMPANY BELIEVES WILL NOT BE COLLECTED.

