NOTE 5

INVESTMENT SECURITIES

INVESTMENT SECURITIES PRINCIPALLY

INCLUDE DEBT SECURITIES THAT THE COMPANY CLASSIFIES AS AVAILABLE-FOR-SALE AND CARRIES AT FAIR VALUE ON THE CONSOLIDATED BALANCE SHEETS, WITH UNREALIZED GAINS (LOSSES) RECORDED IN ACCUMULATED OTHER COMPREHENSIVE LOSS, NET OF INCOME TAXES. REALIZED

GAINS AND LOSSES ARE RECOGNIZED ON A TRADE-DATE BASIS IN RESULTS OF OPERATIONS UPON DISPOSITION OF THE SECURITIES USING THE SPECIFIC IDENTIFICATION METHOD. REFER TO NOTE 15 AND NOTE 19 FOR A DESCRIPTION OF THE COMPANYS METHODOLOGY FOR

DETERMINING THE FAIR VALUE OF INVESTMENT SECURITIES AND GROSS REALIZED GAINS ON THE SALE OF INVESTMENT SECURITIES, RESPECTIVELY.

