THE GROSS UNREALIZED LOSSES ARE ATTRIBUTED TO OVERALL WIDER CREDIT SPREADS FOR STATE AND MUNICIPAL

SECURITIES, WIDER CREDIT SPREADS FOR SPECIFIC ISSUERS, ADVERSE CHANGES IN MARKET BENCHMARK INTEREST RATES, OR A COMBINATION THEREOF, ALL COMPARED TO THOSE PREVAILING WHEN THE INVESTMENT SECURITIES WERE ACQUIRED.

OVERALL, FOR THE INVESTMENT SECURITIES IN GROSS UNREALIZED LOSS POSITIONS, (I) THE COMPANY DOES NOT INTEND TO SELL THE

INVESTMENT SECURITIES, (II) IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE COMPANY WILL NOT BE REQUIRED TO SELL THE INVESTMENT SECURITIES BEFORE RECOVERY OF THE UNREALIZED LOSSES, AND (III) THE COMPANY EXPECTS THAT THE CONTRACTUAL PRINCIPAL AND

INTEREST WILL BE RECEIVED ON THE INVESTMENT SECURITIES. AS A RESULT, THE COMPANY RECOGNIZED NO OTHER-THAN-TEMPORARY IMPAIRMENT DURING THE PERIODS PRESENTED.

