STOCK PLANS

STOCK OPTION AND AWARD PROGRAMS

UNDER THE 2007 INCENTIVE COMPENSATION PLAN AND PREVIOUSLY UNDER THE 1998 INCENTIVE COMPENSATION PLAN, AWARDS MAY BE GRANTED TO

EMPLOYEES AND OTHER KEY INDIVIDUALS WHO PERFORM SERVICES FOR THE COMPANY AND ITS PARTICIPATING SUBSIDIARIES. THESE AWARDS MAY BE IN THE FORM OF STOCK OPTIONS, RESTRICTED STOCK AWARDS OR UNITS (RSAS), PORTFOLIO GRANTS (PGS) OR OTHER INCENTIVES, AND

SIMILAR AWARDS DESIGNED TO MEET THE REQUIREMENTS OF NON-U.S. JURISDICTIONS.

FOR THE COMPANYS INCENTIVE

COMPENSATION PLANS, THERE WERE A TOTAL OF 33 MILLION COMMON SHARES UNISSUED AND AVAILABLE FOR GRANT AS OF DECEMBER 31, 2015, AND 35 MILLION COMMON SHARES UNISSUED AND AVAILABLE FOR GRANT AS OF DECEMBER 31, 2014 AND 2013, AS

AUTHORIZED BY THE COMPANYS BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND SHAREHOLDERS.

