NOTE 20

RESTRUCTURING

FROM TIME TO TIME, THE COMPANY INITIATES

RESTRUCTURING PROGRAMS TO BECOME MORE EFFICIENT AND EFFECTIVE, AND TO SUPPORT NEW BUSINESS STRATEGIES. IN CONNECTION WITH THESE PROGRAMS, THE COMPANY TYPICALLY WILL INCUR SEVERANCE AND OTHER EXIT COSTS.

DURING 2015, THE COMPANY RECORDED A NET REDUCTION OF $26 MILLION IN RESTRUCTURING CHARGES, CONSISTING OF A REDUCTION OF $61 MILLION

IN REVISIONS TO PRIOR ESTIMATES, PARTIALLY OFFSET BY $35 MILLION IN NET RESTRUCTURING CHARGES FOR EG RECORDED IN THE FOURTH QUARTER.

DURING 2014, THE COMPANY RECORDED $411 MILLION OF RESTRUCTURING CHARGES, NET OF REVISIONS TO PRIOR ESTIMATES. THE 2014 ACTIVITY PRIMARILY RELATES TO $313 MILLION AND $133 MILLION OF RESTRUCTURING

CHARGES RECORDED IN THE FOURTH QUARTER AND SECOND QUARTER, RESPECTIVELY.

RESTRUCTURING CHARGES RELATED TO SEVERANCE

OBLIGATIONS ARE INCLUDED IN SALARIES AND EMPLOYEE BENEFITS IN THE COMPANYS CONSOLIDATED STATEMENTS OF INCOME, WHILE CHARGES PERTAINING TO OTHER EXIT COSTS ARE INCLUDED IN OCCUPANCY AND EQUIPMENT AND OTHER EXPENSES.

