THE COMPANY RECORDS A DEFERRED INCOME TAX (BENEFIT) PROVISION WHEN THERE ARE DIFFERENCES BETWEEN ASSETS AND LIABILITIES MEASURED FOR FINANCIAL REPORTING AND FOR INCOME TAX RETURN PURPOSES. THESE

TEMPORARY DIFFERENCES RESULT IN TAXABLE OR DEDUCTIBLE AMOUNTS IN FUTURE YEARS AND ARE MEASURED USING THE TAX RATES AND LAWS THAT WILL BE IN EFFECT WHEN SUCH DIFFERENCES ARE EXPECTED TO REVERSE.

